The first ship in the "Arleigh Burke" class, USS "Arleigh Burke," was commissioned in 1983.
The "Arleigh Burke" class warships were developed by a consortium of shipbuilders including Bath Iron Works, Ingalls Shipbuilding, and Marinette Marine Corporation.
